    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Cornelis de Schepper to Miklós Oláh (Gabela, 6 May 1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">They left Rijeka on 29 April, it took eight days to get
                            here, and they will move on tomorrow. They wanted to go to Dubrovnik,
                            but then due to the Moorish pirates and the plague they came this way
                            instead. He is asking Oláh to forward his letter to his wife.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/A29661E6-B467-4C8B-8D2C-804BBA727A35
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Cornelius Sceperus Nicolao Olao suo salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Reverende et Excellens Domine, Amice et Frater Honorandissime! XXIX.
                    Aprilis solvi ex portu <placeName>Sancti Viti</placeName>. Octavo autem die
                    venimus ad flumen <placeName>Narentam</placeName>,<note xml:id="note.1">The
                        Neretva River.</note> quod labitur in mare non adeo procul ab insula
                        <placeName>Lesina</placeName><note xml:id="note.2">Hvar Island.</note> prope
                        <placeName>Corcyram</placeName>,<note xml:id="note.3">Korčula Island.</note>
                    ubi nunc sumus, cras summo mane hinc abituri. Credebamus autem venire
                        <placeName>Rhagusium</placeName>,<note xml:id="note.4">Dubrovnik.</note> sed
                    ob metum pestis et aliquot biremium Maurarum piraticarum defleximus ad laevam.
                    Estque haec pars <placeName>Bossinae</placeName>. Recte valeo. Intra dies
                    quindecim spero esse <placeName>Constantinopoli</placeName>. Id quod te nolui
                    latere. Nihil habeo, quod scribam, nisi quod te vehementer amo. Litteras unas et
                    breves ad coniugem scripsi. Nam ad alios amicos scribere ob brevitatem temporis
                    non potui. Eas transmittes ad eandem simul et consolaberis miseram cum familia
                    et amicis. Sacrae <persName>reginali maiestati</persName> humillime cupio
                    commendari. Neque minus domino <persName>comiti de Salm</persName>,<note
                        xml:id="note.5">Niklas II, Count of Salm.</note> dominabus <persName>de
                        Baillieul</persName>,<note xml:id="note.6">Madame
                        Bailleul.</note><persName>Lucretiae</persName><note xml:id="note.7">Lucretia
                        Caballis.</note> et si adsit <persName>Honastras</persName>,<note
                        xml:id="note.8">Madame de Souvastre.</note> ceterisque, quibus omnibus
                    felicissima quaeque apprecor. Si potes, commode commendabis et illustribus
                    dominis de <persName>Simpy</persName><note xml:id="note.9">Antoine de
                        Croÿ.</note> et <persName>Molenbays</persName>.<note xml:id="note.10"
                        >Molenbais was probably Seneschal of Queen Mary, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Ortvay</hi> 1914, 345.</note> Nam reverendissimo <persName>domino
                        Panormitano</persName><note xml:id="note.11">Jean II Carondelet.</note> non
                    nunc modo, sed semper cupio esse commendatissimus. Et bene vale, Domine Amice et
                    Frater Observandissime, et me ama.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex <placeName>Gabala</placeName> ad <placeName>Narentam</placeName>
                    VI. Maii 1533.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
